{{distinguish|Octane}}
{{refimprove|date=November 2017}}
[[File:Octan logo.svg|thumb|Octan logo, unchanged since 1992.]]

'''Octan''' is a fictional [[oil company]] that has appeared in multiple [[Lego]] sets since 1992.<ref>{{cite web|title=Sets with "Octan" in the title|url=http://brickset.com/sets?query=Octan|website=Brickset: LEGO Guide and Database|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Sets tagged with "Octan"|url=https://brickset.com/sets/tag-Octan|website=Brickset: LEGO Guide and Database|accessdate=15 February 2018}}</ref> 
Before that time, logos of the real-world oil companies [[Esso]], [[Shell Oil Company|Shell]] and [[Exxon]] were used on sets. The Shell logo continued to be used on promotional sets after that time. In 2014, Lego announced it would not renew its marketing agreement with Shell, under pressure from the environmental group [[Greenpeace]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Lego ends Shell partnership following Greenpeace campaign|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2014/oct/09/lego-ends-shell-partnership-following-greenpeace-campaign|website=The Guardian|accessdate=17 November 2014}}</ref>

''Octan'' (or ''oktan'') is the Danish word for [[octane]], the chemical compound that gives [[gasoline]] its resistance to detonation.

Octan has appeared in a number of [[List of Lego video games|Lego video games]]. ''[[Lego Island]]'' for example features an Octan gas station and the company sponsors the race track. 

In ''[[The Lego Movie]]'', Octan is the base company of the main antagonist Lord Business.  His company is the producer of almost all of the commodities in his dominion.

In the Lego set 7747 Wind Turbine Transport, the Octan logo had a new part in it which said Energy, which implies that it now produces [[renewable energy]], not just oil products. Then, in the set 60016 Tanker Truck, the Energy part of it is larger suggesting that Octan is now going green.

In a number of Town and City sets it is shown that Octan has a racing team that competes in at least Formula One, GT racing and rallying.

