'''Strohschab''' are Austrian costumes representing [[cockroaches]]. They are made of [[hay]] or [[straw]] and are used in Saint Nicholas parades.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.fr/books?id=3ggNDQAAQBAJ&lpg=PT110&ots=coyLPBFY0M&dq=strohschabe&hl=fr&pg=PT110#v=onepage&q=strohschabe&f=false|title=The Krampus and the Old, Dark Christmas: Roots and Rebirth of the Folkloric Devil|last=Ridenour|first=Al|date=2016-09-12|publisher=Feral House|isbn=9781627310413|language=en}}</ref><ref>[http://www.nerdseyeview.com/blog/2004/12/06/if-there-are-cockroaches-it-must-be-christmas/]</ref>
